# Freezed Models

## Basic Entity

```dart
import 'package:freezed_annotation/freezed_annotation.dart';

part 'user.entity.freezed.dart';
part 'user.entity.g.dart'; // Only if using JSON

@freezed
class UserEntity with _$UserEntity {
  const factory UserEntity({
    required String id,
    required String email,
    required String fullName,
    String? avatarUrl,
    @Default(false) bool isVerified,
    @Default([]) List<String> roles,
  }) = _UserEntity;

  factory UserEntity.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) =>
      _$UserEntityFromJson(json);
}
```

### What You Get
- Immutable class with `const` constructor
- `copyWith()` for creating modified copies
- Value equality (`==` and `hashCode`)
- Readable `toString()`
- JSON serialization (if `fromJson` included)

## Sealed Union Types (State Modeling)

```dart
@freezed
sealed class AuthState with _$AuthState {
  const factory AuthState.initial() = AuthInitial;
  const factory AuthState.loading() = AuthLoading;
  const factory AuthState.authenticated(UserEntity user) =
      AuthAuthenticated;
  const factory AuthState.unauthenticated() = AuthUnauthenticated;
  const factory AuthState.error(String message) = AuthError;
}
```

### Consuming with Pattern Matching
```dart
Widget build(BuildContext context, WidgetRef ref) {
  final authState = ref.watch(authNotifierProvider);
  return switch (authState) {
    AuthInitial() => const SplashScreen(),
    AuthLoading() => const LoadingIndicator(),
    AuthAuthenticated(:final user) => HomeScreen(user: user),
    AuthUnauthenticated() => const SignInScreen(),
    AuthError(:final message) => ErrorScreen(message: message),
  };
}
```

## JSON Serialization with snake_case

```dart
@freezed
class ProductDto with _$ProductDto {
  @JsonSerializable(fieldRename: FieldRename.snake)
  const factory ProductDto({
    required String id,
    required String productName,   // maps to product_name
    required double unitPrice,     // maps to unit_price
    @JsonKey(name: 'img_url')
    String? imageUrl,              // custom mapping
  }) = _ProductDto;

  factory ProductDto.fromJson(Map<String, dynamic> json) =>
      _$ProductDtoFromJson(json);
}
```

## Adding Custom Methods

```dart
@freezed
class CartEntity with _$CartEntity {
  const CartEntity._(); // Required for custom methods

  const factory CartEntity({
    @Default([]) List<CartItemEntity> items,
  }) = _CartEntity;

  double get totalPrice =>
      items.fold(0, (sum, item) => sum + item.total);
  bool get isEmpty => items.isEmpty;
}
```

## Code Generation

After creating or modifying any `@freezed` class:

```bash
dart run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs
```

### Part Directives Required
```dart
part '<filename>.freezed.dart';     // Always required
part '<filename>.g.dart';           // Only if using fromJson/toJson
```

## Common Issues

| Issue | Fix |
|-------|-----|
| Missing `.freezed.dart` | Run build_runner |
| `part` directive error | Ensure filename matches exactly |
| Custom methods not working | Add `const ClassName._();` private constructor |
| JSON not generating | Add `part '*.g.dart'` and `fromJson` factory |
| Default value not const | Use `@Default()` with const-compatible values |

## Checklist

- `@freezed` annotation on class
- `with _$ClassName` mixin
- `const factory` constructor
- Correct `part` directives
- `fromJson` factory if JSON needed
- `@JsonSerializable(fieldRename: FieldRename.snake)` for API models
- Private constructor `const ClassName._()` if custom methods
- Entity in domain layer is pure Dart (no Flutter imports)
